I have a friend who had in the toxic relationship, and the bf used to tell her don’t go to the bar even with her female friends. One day, I was with her in downtown then we accidentally met that bf, and she said he’s gonna get mad at me because I told him that I’m home

If you fully trust each other in the relationship, going out with female/male friends is totally ok, I’ll be more anxious if that person lie to me like I’m just gonna go out with my guy friend bla bla bla

Like if you were planning to see friend  but you remember that you have another plan with different friend, then you can just say sorry I forgot that I had another plan with other friend, and I’ll be like oh ok, well then next time!

And unnecessary lie is honestly the worst because that makes me feel like wow you are lying to me, I can’t trust you anymore… I will understand if they tell me honestly, it’s much better than lying for no reason😅

Like when I was with my ex, he lied a millions times, and whenever I asked him, he denied it. After I broke up with him, I heard everything what he was doing behind my back and all of my guess including things I didn’t ask him was right, like literally all of them.

I don’t like when people lie in the situation they don’t have to, and I have a weird talent that I can tell weather that’s a lie or not. When I feel like that person is lying, I’m always right, the proof comes after that.

Growing up with ADHD was really really hard and I was always wondering why I’m different from others especially because I grew up in Japan, where adults force children to be same as others which is fucking insane, I hate it anyway that’s one of the reason I’m not in Japan rn.

And one day we had really hard math homework, and I told my friend it took me too much time to finish and she said me too, so I said “it took me 8 hours” and she was like what? Another moment of realizing. This time I realized I’m not normal :(

The last day of summer/winter break was the worst, I had too much math questions which I didn’t even start, and almost crying but couldn’t tell my mom because if I tell her I didn’t finish, she’s gonna be mad at me.

And I remember how doing homework used to be so hard for me when I was a child, 30 math questions took me 3 hours to finish and felt like killing myself because it was like a torture. Remembering that feeling makes me feel like crying, I’m so happy my mom realized I have ADHD.
Since the day I slowly leaned how to organize my stuff, and now I have an obsession with organizing and cleaning. This is how ADHD with OCD ppl are created lol

Then my childhood bestie Y came to help me to clean my room. I had always fun whenever I’m with her, so it wasn’t so hard to clean my room that day. After we finished cleaning, I was so satisfied, and so happy.

Another moment of realizing, I used to be so not organized child because of ADHD, my room was always messy. One day, my mom told me not to go out until I finish cleaning my room but it was really hard for a child with ADHD, and never actually had finished cleaning

I was wondering why did she say that for few days, but I couldn’t understand why. Then after few days I realized what is death and felt really bad for her, if I have an opportunity, I wanna apologize her.

After that we went to her house, everyone was wearing black and I had a chance to talk to K (my friend), and I asked the dumbest question in my life “hey, are you sad?” I never forget her face at the moment, and she told me “you are the worst person I’ve ever met”
Then I asked her what’s going on? And she said “K’s father passed away”, and I didn’t know how to react, but just surprised.

I clearly remember the moment I heard he passed away, it was Saturday morning, my mom was cleaning the house, and somebody called my home, my mom suddenly dropped the broom, and went to balcony to check my neighbours house, she was like “no you are kidding, I met him yesterday”

And I’m pretty sure the moment I realized the concept of death was after my neighbour passed away, I used to hung out with his daughter a lot so I knew him very well, he used to smoke in front of the house and always had small chat with him before going to school
And I think realizing “what is death” and “what is love” is associated because you love somebody that’s why you are scared of losing them,

The moment I realize something is always cool. Recently I suddenly remember the moment when I realized about death, I was in the bed and suddenly felt so scared of losing my family, and went to my moms room and told her that I’m afraid of losing them
